<br>
A few thoughts:<br>
<br>
Each epic has various stages that can depend highly on whether a mob is even up on the given night.  And not all mobs require zerg level assaults but mainly one or two good teams.  There are some consistant zones in which we all must hunt to acquire epic pieces.<br>
<br>
I might suggest that you consider raiding those zones more often where several classes have needs.  To help define this raid list the LCG members should list the zones where raid numbers are required to obtain the items.<br>
<br>
For example, the shadowknight pieces are located in the planes of air, fear, and hate.  They are also in the Hole, Rathe Mountains, Overthere, and finally City of Mist.<br>
<br>
The Overthere and Rathe Mountains are just a matter of npc rare timer spawn and need one or two good groups.  The Hole, Air, Fear, and Hate however must be found on a raid.  The final battle will take 36 good players to take down the frickin floating lizard in CoM.<br>
<br>
The average number of times a shadowknight has to hit fear is over 20.  The same is true for Hate and the Hole.  Hence much more time is required in these zones.  I suspect most classes have similar tedious raid requirements (Kedge, Karnor, Chardok, etc.).  Therefore we make more epic opportunities by spanking these areas more frequently.<br>
<br>
Just a thought <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Daarth Jheherrin<br>
54 SK<br>
